# Scratch — Quick Notes

A small, dependency-free notes app inspired by the "sticky note" style of
apps like Google Keep, restyled with its own visual identity: a warm
stationery palette, serif display type, and a few extra features
(note colours, pinning, undo-able delete) not found in a bare clone.

Built with plain **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript** — no frameworks, no build
step, no external JS libraries.

## Features

- **Create notes** from the inline composer at the top of the page (title
  is optional).
- **Edit** any note by clicking its card, which opens a modal with the
  full text.
- **Colour** notes using the swatch picker in the composer or the edit
  modal.
- **Pin** important notes so they float to the top of the grid.
- **Archive / Unarchive** notes to tuck them out of the main view without
  deleting them.
- **Delete** moves a note to **Trash** (soft delete, reversible via the
  "Undo" toast).
- **Restore** a note from Trash, or **delete forever** (also reversible
  for a few seconds via "Undo", and Trash can be emptied in bulk).
- **Search** filters notes by title or body across the current view.
- **Grid / list view** toggle, and a collapsible sidebar for small
  screens.
- Notes are saved to the browser's `localStorage`, so they persist
  between visits on the same device/browser.

## Project structure

```
keep-clone/
├── index.html      # Page structure & markup (semantic HTML5)
├── styles.css       # All styling, layout, and responsive rules
├── script.js         # Application logic (state, rendering, events)
├── assets/
│   └── favicon.svg   # Tab icon
└── README.md
```

All icons are inline SVG — there are no external image files to manage
or go missing, and every icon inherits its colour from CSS.

## Running the project

No build tools or installation are required.

**Option 1 — just open it**
Double-click `index.html` (or right-click → Open with your browser).

**Option 2 — local server (recommended)**
Some browsers restrict certain features (like `localStorage`) when a
page is opened directly from the filesystem. A tiny local server avoids
that:

```bash
# from inside the keep-clone folder
python3 -m http.server 8000
# then visit http://localhost:8000 in your browser
```

or, with Node installed:

```bash
npx serve .
```

## Deploying

The app is fully static, so it can be deployed as-is to any static host:

- **GitHub Pages**: push this folder to a repo and enable Pages on the
  `main` branch.
- **Netlify / Vercel**: drag-and-drop the `keep-clone` folder, or connect
  the repo — no build command is needed.

## Notes on the code

- `script.js` is organised into clearly commented sections: persistence,
  helpers, the composer, the edit modal, note actions (archive / delete /
  restore / pin), rendering, and event wiring.
- All user-entered text is HTML-escaped before being rendered, to avoid
  markup injection through note titles or bodies.
- The colour system and typography are defined as CSS custom properties
  at the top of `styles.css`, so the whole palette can be changed from
  one place.